unct in 1992.\n\nFormer U.S. President George W. Bush was a member of Silver Screen Management, Inc.'s board of directors from 1983 to 1993. This became a part of the campaign issue over Hollywood's \"pervasiveness of violence\", centered around Silver Screen Management Board's approval of the highly violent horror-suspense film The Hitcher, when Bush ran for president in 2000. Source: Wikidata; 01/08/2023", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-05T13:56:44.297006+11:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5168, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silver_Screen_Partners"}], "uuid": "1b6a280e-c18a-47dc-912c-a5900968aed8", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "12595", "external_references": [{"id": 26931, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q3483998"}, {"id": 31545, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "312725728"}, {"id": 31546, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no2003041544"}, {"id": 31547, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no2003041544"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-05T13:56:44.297295+11:00"}, {"id": 22847, "name": "Touchstone", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2649143, "title": "Cocktail", "work_id": 80958, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1994967, "title": "Summer of Sam", "work_id": 90781, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2303701, "title": "Snake eyes", "work_id": 90509, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 826479, "title": "True values", "work_id": 96360, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2140194, "title": "Cocktail (Captioned)", "work_id": 84250, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_opera